HEADWORD: Usnic
<hw>Us"nic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Pertaining to, or designating, a complex acid obtained, as a yellow
crystalline substance, from certain genera of lichens (<gen>Usnea</gen>,
<gen>Parmelia</gen>, etc.).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

